Gem Diamonds Says That it Has 28.89 Million Carats of Stones in Resources

-- B y   A m a n d a   J o r d a n
-- 
2011-05-18T06:15:26Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-18/gem-diamonds-says-that-it-has-28-89-million-carats-of-stones-in-resources.html
Gem Diamonds Ltd. (GEMD) , a producer of the
stones in southern  Africa , reported a total resource of 28.89
million carats, valued at an average of $536 a carat.  That increases the in-situ value by 45 percent from a year
earlier to $15.5 billion, or $12.5 billion attributable to the
company, Gem said today in a statement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Amanda Jordan in London at 
 ajordan11@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Amanda Jordan at 
 ajordan11@bloomberg.net  